  "text": "smaller than for NS3pro (data not shown). Much slower relaxation rates in NS2Bc versus NS3pro have similarly been reported for the eZiPro construct . In addition, the chemical shifts of all assigned amide protons of NS2Bc were in the range of 7.6e8.6 ppm, which is characteristic of chemical shifts in flexibly disordered proteins. The chemical shifts were also close to those reported by [CITATION_1] for free NS2B peptide. Therefore, the gZiPro construct used in this work assumes an open conformation in solution, if no high-affinity inhibitor is present.",
